Ing '''malapasi''' (''Chromolaena odorata''), a maki lagyung '''Siam weed''', '''Christmas bush''', and '''common floss flower''' king Ingles, metung yang species ning [[palungpung]] a manyampaga king familiang [[sunflower]] ing [[Asteraceae]]. Katutubu ya king Pangulung America, manibat[[Florida]] ampong [[Texas]] angga king [[Mexico]] ampo ing [[Caribbean]],<ref name="fna">{{cite web | url = http://www.efloras.org/florataxon.aspx?flora_id=1&taxon_id=242312602 | title = Chromolaena odorata | work = Flora of North America }}</ref> at midala ya king malisangan o tropical a dake ning [[Asia]], [[albugan]]g Africa, ampong pilang dake ning [[Australia]]. Neng kayi, tatanam de antimong tanaman a panulu (''medicinal plant'') ampong tanaman a pampasanting (''ornamental plant''). Gagamitan de antimong tradisyonal a panulu king Indonesia. Dadaldakan do reng murang bulung, at gagamitan yang panulu kareng sugat ing makukwang katas. 

Sadya reng yabe king klasipikasyun lalam ning genus ''[[Eupatorium]]'', oneng tuturing deng mas malapit kaugnayan kareng aliwang genus king tribung [[Eupatorieae]].<ref>{{cite journal | title = Phylogeny and Biogeography of Eupatorium (Asteraceae: Eupatorieae) Based on Nuclear ITS Sequence | author = GJ Schmidt, EE Schilling | journal = American Journal of Botany | date = May 2000 | volume = 87 | issue = 5 | pages = 716–726 | url = http://www.amjbot.org/cgi/content/full/87/5/716  | pmid = 10811796 | doi = 10.2307/2656858 | jstor = 2656858 | publisher = Botanical Society of America }}</ref>

Tuturing deng species a mapanyakup (''invasive species'') a dikut da reng tanaman a tatanam kareng asikan king lugal nung nu ya midala  |invasive]] [[weed]] of field crops in its (''introduced range''), at sasabyan dang iti ing pekamaragul a problema kareng species a mapanyakup kareng pulung ingatan (''protected rainforests'') king Africa.<ref>{{cite journal | title = Conserving Africa’s rain forests: problems in protected areas and possible solutions | author = TT Struhsaker, PJ Struhsaker, KS Siex | journal = Biological Conservation | date = May 2005 | volume = 123 | issue = 1 | pages = 45–54 | url = http://rmportal.net/library/content/frame/africas-forest-parks-final-paper.pdf/at_download/file | format= PDF | issn=0006-3207 | doi = 10.1016/j.biocon.2004.10.007}}</ref>

